      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 1918: This public API accepts any non-empty URI authority and uses it directly to select conversations. That means callers can pass malformed or non-Jami URIs, or differently formatted identifiers, and still trigger bootstraps for every matching conversation member. This should validate/canonicalize to the expected Jami account identifier format before using it. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\n    auto peer \u003d std::string(jami::trim(Uri(uri).authority()));\n    if (peer.empty() || !jami::isValidId(peer)) {\n        JAMI_WARNING(\"[Account {}] syncConversationsWith ignored: invalid peer URI \u0027{}\u0027\",\n                     pimpl_-\u003eaccountId_,\n                     uri);\n        return;\n    }\n```",
      "revId": "fd9bbd793ecc5c1840733bd50adc62a092e339d5",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
