      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 1926: Each matching conversation is bootstrapped immediately, with no de-duplication or rate limiting. Because this is exposed through libjami and intended to be called on wake/call events, repeated calls for the same peer can fan out into many reconnect/sync operations and cause avoidable network and CPU load. Consider queuing or coalescing per-peer/per-conversation bootstraps, or skipping conversations already being bootstrapped.",
